Test Cases – AdNabuTestStore
============================

Precondition (applies to all test cases)
---------------------------------------
1. Open the browser  
2. Go to: https://adnabu-store-assignment1.myshopify.com  
3. Enter the store password: AdNabuQA  
4. Click on "Enter" to access the store  

==================================================

(A) Product Search
------------------

TC_01: Search with a valid keyword (Positive)
--------------------------------------------
Priority: High  
Severity: Critical  
Test Data: "iPhone"  

Steps:
1. Open the store using the steps above  
2. Enter "iPhone" in the search bar  
3. Click on search  

Expected Result:
- Products related to "iPhone" should be displayed  
- The results should not be empty  

--------------------------------------------------

TC_02: Search using partial keyword (Positive)
---------------------------------------------
Priority: Medium  
Severity: Major  
Test Data: "iPh"  

Steps:
1. Open the store  
2. Enter "iPh" in the search bar  
3. Click on search  

Expected Result:
- Products matching the partial keyword should be shown  
- Search should still work even with incomplete input  

--------------------------------------------------

TC_03: Search with different case input (Positive)
-------------------------------------------------
Priority: Low  
Severity: Minor  
Test Data: "iphone"  

Steps:
1. Open the store  
2. Enter "iphone" in lowercase  
3. Click on search  

Expected Result:
- Search should work regardless of letter case  
- Correct products should still be displayed  

--------------------------------------------------

TC_04: Search with invalid keyword (Negative)
--------------------------------------------
Priority: Medium  
Severity: Major  
Test Data: "xyz123ABC!@#$"  

Steps:
1. Open the store  
2. Enter an invalid/random keyword  
3. Click on search  

Expected Result:
- A message like "No results found" should be shown  
- No unrelated products should appear  

--------------------------------------------------

TC_05: Search without entering anything (Edge Case)
--------------------------------------------------
Priority: Medium  
Severity: Minor  
Test Data: Empty input  

Steps:
1. Open the store  
2. Leave the search field empty  
3. Click on search  

Expected Result:
- Either a validation message should be shown  
  OR all products may be displayed (depending on design)  
- Application should not crash  

==================================================

(B) Add to Cart
---------------

TC_06: Add an in-stock product to cart (Positive)
------------------------------------------------
Priority: High  
Severity: Critical  
Test Data: Product from "iPhone" search  

Steps:
1. Open the store  
2. Search for "iPhone"  
3. Open any available product  
4. Click on "Add to Cart"  

Expected Result:
- Product should be added successfully  
- Cart count should increase  
- Product should be visible in the cart  

--------------------------------------------------

TC_07: Add multiple different products (Positive)
------------------------------------------------
Priority: Medium  
Severity: Major  
Test Data: Two different products  

Steps:
1. Open the store  
2. Add one product to the cart  
3. Add another product  

Expected Result:
- Both products should be added  
- Cart should show correct number of items  

--------------------------------------------------

TC_08: Try adding an out-of-stock product (Negative)
---------------------------------------------------
Priority: High  
Severity: Major  
Test Data: Out-of-stock product  

Steps:
1. Open the store  
2. Open a product that is out of stock  
3. Click on "Add to Cart"  

Expected Result:
- System should show a proper message  
- Product should not be added to the cart  

--------------------------------------------------

TC_09: Add to cart without selecting required options (Negative)
---------------------------------------------------------------
Priority: Medium  
Severity: Major  
Test Data: Product with size or color  

Steps:
1. Open the store  
2. Open a product that has required options  
3. Do not select any option  
4. Click on "Add to Cart"  

Expected Result:
- A validation message should be shown  
- Product should not be added  

--------------------------------------------------

TC_10: Add the same product multiple times (Edge Case)
-----------------------------------------------------
Priority: Medium  
Severity: Major  
Test Data: Same product  

Steps:
1. Open the store  
2. Add the same product multiple times  

Expected Result:
- Quantity should increase properly  
- Duplicate entries should not be created  
